Package: odrive-linux
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
 libgtk-4-1 (>= 4.12),
 libadwaita-1-0 (>= 1.5),
 wl-clipboard | xclip,
 xdg-utils,
 curl,
Recommends:
 gnome-shell-extension-appindicator,
Suggests:
 odrive-linux-nautilus,
 odrive-linux-dolphin,
Description: Linux frontend for odrive on-demand cloud sync
 odrive-linux is a native Linux manager around odrive's headless agent
 (odriveagent) and CLI (odrive). It ships a GTK4/Libadwaita Manager,
 a Rust CLI, an onboarding wizard that downloads and registers the
 official agent on first launch, MIME registrations for *.cloud /
 *.cloudf placeholder files, and a system-tray indicator.
 .
 Install odrive-linux-nautilus or odrive-linux-dolphin alongside this
 package for first-class right-click integration in your file manager.
 .
 GNOME 46+ or KDE Plasma 6.0+ recommended.

Package: odrive-linux-nautilus
Architecture: all
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 odrive-linux (= ${binary:Version}),
Recommends:
 python3-nautilus,
Description: Nautilus right-click integration for odrive-linux
 Python extension that adds an "Odrive" submenu to Nautilus's
 right-click menu (Sync, Unsync, Refresh, Share Storage, Copy Share
 Link, Open Web Preview) and emblem decorations on placeholders and
 synced files.
 .
 Requires python3-nautilus to actually load — install that package or
 your Nautilus session won't see the extension.

Package: odrive-linux-dolphin
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
 odrive-linux (= ${binary:Version}),
Recommends:
 dolphin,
Description: Dolphin right-click integration for odrive-linux
 Qt6/KF6 KFileItemAction and KOverlayIcon plugins giving Dolphin
 first-class odrive integration: an "Odrive" right-click submenu
 that filters to in-mount selections, plus per-file emblem overlays
 for synced and syncing items.
 .
 Plasma 6.0 or newer required.
